Chapter 3 – Proposed Architecture: Neural World Simulation Engine (NWSE)

3.1 Notation and Overview

Let \mathbf{o}_t \in \mathbb{R}^{D_{\text{sensor}}} be the multimodal observation, \mathbf{a}_t \in \mathbb{R}^{D_{\text{act}}} the action, r_t \in \mathbb{R} the reward (optional). The NWSE maintains a latent belief composed of:

· Deterministic recurrent state \mathbf{h}_t \in \mathbb{R}^{D_h},
· Stochastic latent \mathbf{z}_t (categorical with N_z classes),
· Dynamic scene graph \mathcal{G}_t = (\mathcal{V}_t, \mathcal{E}_t) with node descriptors \mathbf{l}_v^{(t)} \in \mathbb{R}^{D_l} and poses \mathbf{p}_v^{(t)} \in SE(3), and edge transforms \mathbf{T}_{uv} \in SE(3),
· Memory matrix \mathbf{M}_t \in \mathbb{R}^{N_m \times D_m}.

3.2 Multimodal Encoder and Graph Construction

Modality‑specific encoders produce embeddings \mathbf{e}_t^{\text{mod}}. A cross‑attention fusion yields joint observation \mathbf{x}_t:

\mathbf{x}_t = \text{CrossAttn}\left( Q = \text{Linear}(\mathbf{e}_t^{\text{vis}}),\; K = \text{Linear}(\mathbf{e}_t^{\text{aud}}),\; V = \text{Linear}(\mathbf{e}_t^{\text{hap}}) \right).

An object discovery module extracts initial nodes. A Graph Neural Network (GNN) refines the graph via message passing:

\mathbf{m}_v^{(l)} = \sum_{u \in \mathcal{N}(v)} \text{MLP}_{\text{msg}}(\mathbf{h}_u^{(l-1)}, \mathbf{e}_{uv}), \quad
\mathbf{h}_v^{(l)} = \text{GRU}(\mathbf{h}_v^{(l-1)}, \mathbf{m}_v^{(l)}),

where \mathbf{e}_{uv} encodes relative pose \mathbf{T}_{uv} and relation type. After L layers, node embeddings become \mathbf{l}_v^{(t)}.

3.3 Memory‑Augmented Recurrent State‑Space Model (MA‑RSSM)

The deterministic state update reads from memory:

\mathbf{r}_t = \text{Read}(\mathbf{M}_{t-1}, \mathbf{h}_{t-1}) = \text{CrossAttn}(Q = \mathbf{h}_{t-1}, K = \mathbf{M}_{t-1}, V = \mathbf{M}_{t-1}),

\mathbf{h}_t = \text{GRU}_{\phi}(\mathbf{h}_{t-1}, [\mathbf{z}_{t-1}, \mathbf{a}_{t-1}, \mathbf{r}_t]).

Stochastic state:

· Prior: \hat{\mathbf{z}}_t \sim p_\phi(\hat{\mathbf{z}}_t \mid \mathbf{h}_t) = \text{Cat}(\boldsymbol{\pi}_t^{\text{prior}}).
· Posterior: \mathbf{z}_t \sim q_\phi(\mathbf{z}_t \mid \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{x}_t) = \text{Cat}(\boldsymbol{\pi}_t^{\text{post}}).

Surprise‑driven memory write: Compute d_t = \mathrm{KL}[q_\phi \| p_\phi]. If d_t > \tau, write (\mathbf{k}_t, \mathbf{v}_t) to memory using LRU replacement:

\mathbf{k}_t = \text{MLP}_k([\mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{z}_t]), \quad \mathbf{v}_t = \text{MLP}_v([\mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{z}_t]).

Generative model:

\hat{\mathbf{x}}_t \sim p_\phi(\hat{\mathbf{x}}_t \mid \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{z}_t), \quad
\hat{r}_t \sim p_\phi(\hat{r}_t \mid \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{z}_t), \quad
\hat{\mathcal{G}}_t \sim p_\phi(\hat{\mathcal{G}}_t \mid \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{z}_t).

3.4 Graph Dynamics as Part of the Latent State

The scene graph evolves via a Graph Recurrent Network (GRN):

\tilde{\mathcal{G}}_t = \text{GRN}(\mathcal{G}_{t-1}, \mathbf{a}_{t-1}, \mathbf{h}_t),

with node update:

\mathbf{l}_v^{(t)} = \text{GRU}_{\text{node}}\left( \mathbf{l}_v^{(t-1)},\; \sum_{u \in \mathcal{N}(v)} \text{MLP}_{\text{edge}}(\mathbf{l}_u^{(t-1)}, \mathbf{T}_{uv}^{(t-1)}) \right).

3.5 Unified ELBO with Graph and Memory Regularization

Let \mathbf{Z}_t = (\mathbf{z}_t, \mathcal{G}_t, \mathbf{M}_t) be the joint latent. The evidence lower bound becomes:

\begin{aligned}
\log p(\mathbf{o}_{1:T}, r_{1:T} \mid \mathbf{a}_{1:T-1}) &\geq \sum_{t=1}^T \mathbb{E}_{q} \Big[ \log p(\mathbf{o}_t, r_t \mid \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{z}_t) + \log p(\mathcal{G}_t \mid \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{z}_t) \Big] \\
&\quad - \sum_{t=1}^T \mathrm{KL}\big( q(\mathbf{z}_t \mid \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{x}_t) \| p(\mathbf{z}_t \mid \mathbf{h}_t) \big) \\
&\quad - \sum_{t=1}^T \mathrm{KL}\big( q(\mathcal{G}_t \mid \mathbf{o}_t, \mathcal{G}_{t-1}) \| p(\mathcal{G}_t \mid \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{z}_t) \big) \\
&\quad - \sum_{t=1}^T \mathbb{E}_{q} \left[ \mathrm{KL}\big( q(\mathbf{M}_t \mid \mathbf{M}_{t-1}, \Delta_t) \| p(\mathbf{M}_t \mid \mathbf{M}_{t-1}) \big) \right],
\end{aligned}

where \Delta_t = \mathrm{KL}[q_\phi \| p_\phi] is the surprise signal, and p(\mathbf{M}_t \mid \mathbf{M}_{t-1}) is a diffusion-style prior that softly decays unused slots.

3.6 Self‑Supervised Predictive Objective for Intuitive Physics

Inspired by V-JEPA, we add a loss that predicts latent representations of masked future observations:

\mathcal{L}_{\text{pred}} = \mathbb{E}_{\text{mask}} \sum_{t \in \text{mask}} \left\| \text{sg}\big( f_{\theta_{\text{EMA}}}(\mathbf{o}_{1:t}^{\text{unmasked}}) \big) - p_{\phi}^{\text{pred}}(\{\mathbf{z}_{<t}^{\text{unmasked}}\}) \right\|_1.

3.7 Complexity Analysis

Component Standard RSSM Transformer‑only NWSE (Proposed)
Temporal complexity O(T) O(T^2) O(T \log N_m)
Spatial complexity (per step) O(1) O(N_{\text{pixels}}) O(K^2) (where K = \#\text{objects})
Memory (long‑term) None O(T) O(N_m) with N_m \ll T

